                   @{"            Description!            " link 1}

 In brief, BBS-Advert is simply a MAXs Door that displays adverts/bulletins.

@endnode
@node 2 " BBS-ADVERT GUiDE (c)1996 Glen Martin    [Page 2 of 5] "
@prev 1
@next 3

                   @{"            Installation            " link 2}

 Very simple indeed, Unpack the BBS-Advert archive into your Doors directory.
 Text edit the file BBS-ADVERT.bbs and put your Name and BBS Name/Details.

@endnode
@node 3 " BBS-ADVERT GUiDE (c)1996 Glen Martin    [Page 3 of 5] "
@prev 2
@next 4

                   @{"            Instructions            " link 3}

 Ummmm, You should have the following files in the BBS-Advert directory:
 Adds (directory containing adds), BBS-ADVERT.prompt (Door Ask Prompt),
 BBS-ADVERT.bbs (your bbs rego), BBS-ADVERT! (execute file/Door).
 The directory Adds is where you put your adverts/bulletins and they must
 be in number sequence, and named BBS-Advert.01 (up to .10) [Refer to the
 examples]. You can Either run the Door upon Login or from a Menu. If you
 run the Door during Login and want the Ask Prompt for users, then make
 sure BBS-ADVERT.prompt is present, otherwise rename it/delete it so to
 remove the Ask Prompt. Play around with the Door as it's not hard to run!

@endnode
